\n| ShortSummary    = \u00c9l\u00e9a and C\u00e9dric, placing first and second respectively, became the first Influencers.\n*'''Game (\"D'accord, pas d'accord?\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Agree or Disagree?\")''': Players were given statements and had to say whether they agree or disagree with the statements. After all the players had answered, the results were revealed and the players were allowed to discuss their answers.\nThat night, \u00c9l\u00e9a and C\u00e9dric went to the Hangout to discuss their decision. Meanwhile, those in danger entered the At Risk Chat to talk. \u00c9l\u00e9a and C\u00e9dric decided to block Lou. After being blocked, Lou visited C\u00e9dric to talk face-to-face. The next morning, The Circle posted a goodbye message from Lou.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Blocked|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062036?trackId=200257858|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=2}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = #cgolri\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = A new player, Rudy entered The Circle, playing as Gabriel.\n*'''Game (\"Cin\u00e9mojis\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Cinema [[Emoji|Emojis]]\")''': Players were given a string of emojis to represent a movie title. Players had to guess the movie title, and then answer a question pertaining to that movie. The highest scoring players earned a private party with Rudy. Gary, Ines, and Maxime were the highest scoring players.\nThe next day, the ratings opened. Rudy, being the newest player in The Circle, could rate but could not be rated. Ines and Maxime became Influencers, placing first and second respectively.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=#cgolri|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062037?trackId=200257858|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=3}}</ref>\n| LineColor      