e two lowest rated players, \u00c9l\u00e9a and C\u00e9dric, went to the Hangout where they saw each other face-to-face. C\u00e9dric received three of the five available votes, meaning he was blocked. Soon after, Paolo entered The Circle. The players had to write a handwritten card to send the Paolo. After, they were uploaded to the newsfeed for everyone to see.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Knocked Out|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062040?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=6}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Alliances\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = Paolo was able to send one gift, either a teddy bear, a box of chocolates, or a bouquet, to whoever's message made this biggest impact on him. He decided to send the box of chocolates to Romain.\n*'''Game (\"Soir\u00e9e Pyjama\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"Pajama Party\")''': The players were given their own pair of matching pajamas. Through the night, the players were allowed to have a pajama party with each other, engaging in chats and dancing to music. The next morning, the ratings opened. With Paolo being the newest player, he could rate the others but he was not allowed to be rated. Then the ratings were revealed. \u00c9l\u00e9a and Ines, placing first and second respctively, became the Influencers.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Alliances|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=7}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = The Last 8\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = \u00c9l\u00e9a and Ines decided to block Gary. Gary decided to visit Ines, meeting face-to-face. The next morning, Gary's goodbye message was posted on the newsfeed. That same day, the last player, Virginie, entered The Circle.\n*'''Game (\"Le Plus Beau Portrait G\u00e2teau\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"The Best Looking Will Get What's Cooking\")''': The players had to bake a cake that bore the effigy of Virginie. Virginie would pick the best looking cake. She decided \u00c9l\u00e9a's cake was the best.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Last 8|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=8}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = The Super Influencer\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The players were informed that Virginie was the last player to join The Circle. They were also told that the next rating would not have two Influencers, but just one \"Superinfluencer\" who would have the power to block any player of their choosing. The ratings opened, and since Virginie was the newest player, she could rate but could not be rated. Romain became the Superinfluencer, and he decided to block Ines. The next morning, the newsfeed was updated with Ines' goodbye message.\n*'''Game (\"La V\u00e9rit\u00e9, Rien Que La V\u00e9rit\u00e9?\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"The Truth, Nothing but the Truth?\")''': One at a time, the players was asked a question pertaining to one of the players. After all of the players answered the question, the results were revealed.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Super Infulencer|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=9}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = The Betrayal\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The ratings opened with another rule change. The least popular player would be instantly blocked. Paolo was the lowest rated player, and he was blocked. Paolo went to visit Edmundo & Jo\u00e3o. The next morning, the newsfeed was updated with Paolo's goodbye video. Soon after, the players were allowed to post a new photo to their profile.\n*'''Game (\"Circle Challenges\")''': The players were given a series of challenges. The winner of each challenge could eliminate two players until there were two left. The winner of the last challenge won a video from their family. They could also choose one other player to receive a video from home. \u00c9l\u00e9a won, and she also gave a video from home to Maxime.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Betrayal|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=10}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n| Title           = No Filter\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The ratings opened. These ratings determined who advanced to the finale. The next morning, the ratings were revealed. Romain and \u00c9lea, placing first and second respectively, and became the last Influencers of the season.\n*'''Game (\"Le Quart D'heure No Fliter\", {{abbr|lit.|Literal translation in English}} \"The No Filter Quarter Hour\")''': Players could anonymously ask one player a question, which they can answer however they choose to. After the player answers, the chat opens to everyone to give their thoughts on the question.\nRomain and \u00c9lea decided to block Virginie.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=No Filter|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=11}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = The Finale\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The players entered their ratings for the final time. Then, the players, as part of finale night, all went to one room to meet each other face-to-face for the first time during the whole game. Romain entered first, followed by Maxime, \u00c9l\u00e9a, and Rudy. Edmundo & Jo\u00e3o entered the room last. Then, one at a time, they entered the living room, where all of the blocked players were waiting. Before the ratings were revealed, the final five players were informed that all of the final eight players had taken part in the final ratings, including Virginie, Paolo, and Ines. Romain, earning first place, became the winner of ''The Circle France''.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=The Finale|url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81062041?trackId=155573558|series=The Circle France|network=[[Netflix]]|date=9 April 2020|season=1|number=12}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = EE6161\n}}\n}}\n\n== Background ==\n=== Concept ===\nTim Harcourt is the creative director of [[Studio Lambert]], which produces the British and American versions of the show. Harcourt wondered what a [[Reality competition|reality show]] would look like if the people never met face-to-face. He had also been considering the idea of a [[bird's-eye view]]-style documentary of an apartment building, seeing into each of their lives. He began to work on ''[[The Circle (franchise)|The Circle]]'' after hearing that [[Channel 4]] was looking for a reality-show format centered on social media.<ref name=\"insider\">{{cite web |last1=Smallman |first1=Etan |title=Inside 'The Circle,' Reality TV Gets a Social Media Filter |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/29/arts/television/the-circle-netflix.html |website=nytimes.com |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=30 December 2019 |location=London, United Kingdom |date=29 December 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Development ===\n[[The Circle (British TV series)|The British version]] of the show premiered in 2018, and was renewed for its second season a few months after the first season ended.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tutton|first1=Charlotte|title=The Circle season 2 confirmed as Channel 4 series returns with a HUGE twist|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/tv/1541465/the-circle-season-2-channel-4-series-return-new-twists-live-episode-how-long-on-prize-money-win|website=OK! Magazine|accessdate=19 January 2019 |date=18 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ling|first1=Thomas|title=The Circle series 2 confirmed \u2013 but there are going to be some changes|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-01-18/the-circle-series-2-channel-4-confirmed-how-to-apply|website=Radio Times|accessdate=19 January 2019|language=en}}</ref> After the first season was [[Channel 4]]'s \"youngest profiling\" show in six years, according to the British TV industry magazine ''[[Broadcast (magazine)|Broadcast]]'', talks began of international versions.<ref name=\"insider\"/> On October 8, 2018, [[Netflix]] announced its partnership with [[All3Media]] to create three international versions of ''The Circle'' on Netflix, including the American version. Brandon Reigg, Netflix's Vice Principal of Unscripted Content, stated, \"We think the show's combination of modern social media interaction and competition will captivate Netflix members around the world, in multiple languages, and we're delighted to partner with Studio Lambert and Motion to produce these three new local versions.\"<ref name=\"adaptation\">{{cite web|url=https://media.netflix.com/en/press-releases/netflix-to-adapt-uk-unscripted-sensation-the-circle-with-three-local-versions-for-countries-around-the-world|title=Netflix to Adapt UK Unscripted Sensation ''The Circle'' with Three Local Versions for Countries Around the World|date=8 October 2018|publisher=Netflix Media Center|location=Hollywood, California|url-status=live|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Production == \n=== Casting ===\nIn an interview with ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', Tim Harcourt, one of the executive producers for [[Studio Lambert]], stated that ''The Circle'' format and premise allowed the casting team to search for all different kinds of people. He noted how the casting contrasted from casts on show like ''[[Real Housewives]]'' or ''[[Jersey Shore (TV series)|Jersey Shore]]'' and how those shows are \"all one gang of quite similar characters.\"<ref name=\"variety interview\">{{cite web |last1=Turchiano |first1=Danielle |title='The Circle' Boss on Connecting 'People Who Otherwise Might Not Have Come into Contact with Each Other' \u2014 And Catfishing |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/features/the-circle-netflix-american-tim-harcourt-catfish-interview-1203449625/ |website=variety.com |publisher=Variety |accessdate=2 January 2020 |date=1 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> He explained how there was no set cast for the show until it was over. The first eight players to enter were all predetermined and planned, but everything after that was all luck to whoever got on. Harcourt stated that the production team would decide who would be the right fit depending on who just left the game, acknowledging that with thirteen contestants, not all who were possible players end up on the show at all.<ref name=\"variety interview\"/>\n\nJennifer Teixido was the casting director for ''The Circle France''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jennifer TEIXIDO |url=https://fr.linkedin.com/in/jenn-teixido |publisher=Linkedin |accessdate=8 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jenn Teixido \ud83c\udfac Directrice des castings @tf1 . Directrice de casting @thecirclenetflix France . The Circle Game France - 9 avril sur @netflixfr \u2b55\ufe0f |url=https://www.instagram.com/jenn.teixido/ |website=instagram.com |publisher=Instagram |accessdate=8 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== The Circle app ===\nEach apartment that the players live in is plastered with screens in every room in order for the players be able to hold conversations with other players as they go about their everyday lives. Each player starts out the game by creating a profile. This includes sharing their age, [[relationship status]], a short [[biography|bio]], and one photo to use as their [[Avatar (computing)|profile picture]]. Everyday, the players are allowed to share a status update, explaining their thoughts for the day. Sometimes, either through rewards or passing a certain milestone, the players are allowed to upload another photo to their profile.<ref name=\"variety interview\"/> However, the main purpose of The Circle (\"du Cercle\" in [[French language|French]]) is to be the only way players can communicate with each other.<ref name=\"variety interview\"/>\n\nAt several points during the game, usually every episode, The Circle has the players play a [[minigame]] so that they can get to know their fellow players better. Tim Harcourt of [[Studio Lambert]] says that \"some games were really good for bonding them, some were really good for them learning about each other, some were good for testing who's a catfish, some could have been more divisive.\"<ref name=\"variety interview\"/>\n\nAt certain points during the show, there would be a rating. Players would have to rate each other from first to last by using The Circle and announcing the players they want in each placement. Then, the ratings would be averaged and create an average placement for each player. Depending on how high or low their average placement was, the player's ranking would determine if they became in influencer or not. An influencer is usually the two people who get first and second place at the ratings. The influencers would head to the hangout and discuss over The Circle which person to block.<ref name=\"variety interview\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Fallo |first1=Julie |title=The Circle: US Version Has a Shot at Succeeding From All the Right Changes |url=https://screenrant.com/circle-us-version-success-changes/ |website=screenrant.com |publisher=Screen Rant |accessdate=15 January 2020 |date=3 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n''The Circle France'' was filmed in December 2019, in the same [[Salford|Salford, England]] apartment building that was also used by [[The Circle (American TV series)|American version]]'s [[The Circle (American season 1)|first season]], the [[The Circle (British TV series)|British version]]'s [[The Circle (British series 2)|second season]], and the [[The Circle (Brazilian TV series)|Brazilian version's first season]]. The season was the last of those four seasons filmed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/how-the-circle-works-creator-tim-harcourt.html|title=The Circle\u2019s Creator Guides Us Through the Show\u2019s Beautiful Web of Lies|last=Haylock|first=Zoe|date=2020-01-21|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Release ===\nOn 26 March 2020, the trailer for the French version was released, revealing the premiere date to be 9 April 2020, and the prize amount to be [[Euro|\u20ac]]100,000 ({{USD|110000}}).<ref name=\"trailer\"/> All twelve episodes dropped on 9 April; this is different from all other versions which released several episodes weekly.\n\n== Results and elimination ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|+ <big>'''Color Key'''</big>\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was blocked.\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightgreen; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was an influencer.\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FBF373; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| The contestant was immune from being blocked.\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:100%; font-size:90%; line-height:15px;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:7%;\" |\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep1|Episode 1]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep3|Episode 3]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep6|Episode 6]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep7|Episode 7]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep9|Episode 9]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep10|Episode 10]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep11|Episode 11]]\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:7%;\" | [[#ep12|Episode 12<br>Finale]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000\" colspan=\"10\"|\n|-\n! Romain\n| '''3rd'''\n| '''5th'''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | '''4th'''\n| '''=4th'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | ''Not<br>published''\n| '''2nd'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''1st'''\n| '''1st'''\n| style=\"background:gold;\" | '''Winner'''<br>{Episode 12)\n|-\n! \u00c9l\u00e9a\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''1st'''\n| '''7th'''\n| '''6th'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''1st'''\n| ''Not<br>published''\n| '''4th'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''2nd'''\n| '''2nd'''\n| style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Second place'''<br>(Episode 12)\n|-\n! Rudy<br><small>\"Gabriel\"</small>\n| bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | ''Not in<br>The Circle''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | ''Exempt''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | '''2nd'''\n| '''3rd'''\n| ''Not<br>published''\n| '''5th'''\n| '''5th'''\n| '''3rd'''\n| style=\"background:tan;\" | '''Third place'''<br>(Episode 12)\n|-\n! Edmundo & Jo\u00e3o<br><small>\"Nelia\"</small>\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | ''Not in<br>The Circle''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373\"| ''Exempt''\n| '''7th'''\n| ''Not<br>published''\n| '''6th'''\n| '''6th'''\n| '''4th'''\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | '''Fourth place'''<br>(Episode 12)\n|-\n! Maxime<br><small>\"Valeria\"</small>\n| '''7th'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''1st'''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | '''1st'''\n| '''6th'''\n| ''Not<br>published''\n| '''3rd'''\n| '''4th'''\n| '''5th'''\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | '''Fifth place'''<br>(Episode 12)\n|-\n! Virginie\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | ''Not in<br>The Circle''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373\"| ''Exempt''\n| '''1st'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''3rd'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"2\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 11)\n|-\n! Paolo\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"lightgrey\" | ''Not in<br>The Circle''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373\"| ''Exempt''\n| ''Not<br>published''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''7th'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"3\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 10)\n|-\n! Ines\n| '''=4th'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''2nd'''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | '''3rd'''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''2nd'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | ''Not<br>published''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"4\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 9)\n|-\n! Gary\n| '''=4th'''\n| '''3rd'''\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | '''5th'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''=4th'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"5\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 8)\n|-\n! C\u00e9dric\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | '''2nd'''\n| '''4th'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''7th'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"6\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 6)\n|-\n! Jo & Monique<br><small>\"Nicholas\"</small>\n| '''8th'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''6th'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"7\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 4)\n|-\n! Lou\n| style=\"background:pink;\" | '''6th'''\n| style=\"background:salmon\" colspan=\"8\" | ''Blocked''<br>(Episode 2)\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000\" colspan=\"10\"|\n|-\n! Notes\n| colspan=\"2\" | ''none''\n| ''[[#endnote 1|1]]''\n| ''none''\n| ''[[#endnote 2|2]]''\n| ''[[#endnote 3|3]]''\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''none''\n|-\n! Influencers\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"| C\u00e9dric<br>\u00c9l\u00e9a\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"| Ines<br>Maxime\n| ''none''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"| \u00c9l\u00e9a<br>Ines\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"| Romain\n| ''none''\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"| \u00c9l\u00e9a<br>Romain\n| colspan=\"2\"| ''none''\n|-\n! rowspan=3|Blocked\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Lou'''<br><small>Influencers'<br>choice to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Jo & Monique<br><small>\"Nicholas\"</small>'''<br><small>Influencers'<br>choice to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''C\u00e9dric'''<br><small>3 of 5 votes<br>to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Gary'''<br><small>Influencers'<br>choice to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Ines'''<br><small>Superinfluencer's<br>choice to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Paolo'''<br><small>Lowest<br>rated player</small>\n| style=\"background:#FA8072\" rowspan=3|'''Virginie'''<br><small>Influencers'<br>choice to block</small>\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80\"|'''Maxime<br><small>\"Valeria\"</small>'''<br><small>Lowest<br />rated player</small>\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80\"|'''{{nowrap|Edmundo & Jo\u00e3o}}<br><small>\"Nelia\"</small>'''<br><small>{{nowrap|Fourth highest}}<br />rated player</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:tan\"|'''Rudy<br><small>\"Gabriel\"</small>'''<br><small>{{nowrap|Third highest}}<br />rated player</small>\n| style=\"background:silver\"|'''\u00c9l\u00e9a'''<br><small>Second highest<br />rated player</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:gold\" colspan=\"2\"|'''Romain'''<br><small>Highest<br />rated player</small>\n|}\n\n=== Notes ===\n<small>\n*{{note|1|Note 1}}: In Episode 5, there were no Influencers. Instead, the two lowest rated players were at risk and were the only ones that could be blocked. The five other players, excluding Edmundo & Jo\u00e3o had to decide which of the two would be blocked. Romain, Maxime and Rudy chose to block C\u00e9dric, and Ines and Gary chose to block \u00c9l\u00e9a. Since C\u00e9dric received more votes, he was blocked.\n*{{note|2|Note 2}}: In Episode 9, the ratings were not published. Instead, the highest-rated player automatically became the \"Superinfluencer\", who could make the sole decision on whom to block.\n*{{note|3|Note 3}}: In Episode 10, there were no Influencers. Instead, the least popular player was instantly blocked.\n</small>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Netflix title|81044719}}\n* [https://www.instagram.com/circlegame/ @circlegame] on [[Instagram]]\n\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n{{The Circle (franchise)|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Circle French TV Series}}\n[[Category:2010s reality television series]]\n[[Category:French reality television series]]\n[[Category:French-language television programs]]\n[[Category:French-language Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:The Circle (TV series)]]\n", "name_user": "Jayab314", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eResults and elimination", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Circle_(French_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Geoff Dyer", "text_new": "{{For|the Australian painter|Geoffrey Dyer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox writer\n|name          = Geoff Dyer\n|image         = Geoff Dyer 2015.jpg\n|image_size    = \n|alt           = \n|caption       = Dyer at the 2015 Texas Book Festival\n|birth_name    = \n|birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1958|6|5|df=y}}\n|birth_place   = [[Cheltenham]], [[Gloucestershire]], England\n|residence     = [[Venice, Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n|nationality   = British\n|education     = \n|alma_mater    = [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford]]\n|years_active  = \n|notable_works =\n|style         = \n|home_town     = Cheltenham, Gloucestershire, England\n|spouse        = \n|children      = \n|parents       = \n|relations     = \n|callsign      =\n|awards        =\n|signature     =\n|signature_alt =\n|website       =\n|footnotes     =\n}}\n\n'''Geoff Dyer''' (born 5 June 1958) is an English writer. He has authored a number of novels and books of non-fiction, which have won literary awards and been translated into 24 languages. [[Kathryn Schulz]], writing in ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'', described him as \"one of our greatest living critics, not of the arts but of life itself, and one of our most original writers\".<ref>[https://www.vulture.com/2014/05/book-review-another-great-day-at-sea.html New York Magazine]</ref>\n\n==Personal background==\nDyer was born and raised in [[Cheltenham]], England, as the only child of a [[sheet metal]] worker father and a [[Lunch lady|school dinner lady]] mother. He was educated at the local grammar school and won a scholarship to study English at [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford]]. He is married to [[Rebecca Wilson (curator)|Rebecca Wilson]], chief curator at [[Saatchi Art]], Los Angeles.<ref>He currently lives in Venice, California. {{cite news | author=Geoff Dyer | title=I am What I am: Geoff Dyer | date=29 March 2009 | work=[[The Sunday Times]] | url=http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/the_way_we_live/article5966843.ece | accessdate=2011-05-09 | location=London}}</ref> In March 2014, Dyer said he had had a minor stroke earlier in the year, shortly after moving to live in [[Venice, Los Angeles]].<ref>Dyer, Geoff [http://www.lrb.co.uk/v36/n07/geoff-dyer/diary ''Diary''] [[London Review of Books]], Vol. 36 No. 7 \u2013 3 April 2014.</ref>\n\n==Writing career==\nDyer is the author of four novels: ''The Colour of Memory;'' ''The Search;'' ''Paris Trance;'' and, most recently, ''Jeff in Venice, Death in Varanasi''. He wrote a critical study of John Berger \u2013 ''Ways of Telling \u2013'' and two collections of essays: ''Anglo-English Attitudes'' and ''Working the Room''.  A selection of essays from these collections entitled ''Otherwise Known as the Human Condition'' was published in the U.S. in April 2011 and won the [[National Book Critics Circle Award]] for Criticism.\n\nDyer wrote seven genre-defying titles: ''But Beautiful'' (on jazz); ''The Missing of the Somme'' (on the memorialization of the First World War); ''Out of Sheer Rage'' (about [[D. H. Lawrence]]); ''Yoga For People Who Can\u2019t Be Bothered To Do It;'' ''The Ongoing Moment'' (on photography); ''Zona'' (about [[Andrei Tarkovsky]]\u2019s 1979 film ''[[Stalker (1979 film)|Stalker]]''); and ''Broadsword Calling Danny Boy'' (about [[Brian G. Hutton]]'s 1968 film ''[[Where Eagles Dare]]''). He is the editor of ''John Berger: Selected Essays'' and co-editor, with Margaret Sartor, of ''What Was True: The Photographs and Notebooks of William Gedney''.\n\nOne of his most recent books, ''Another Great Day at Sea'' (2014), chronicles Dyer\u2019s experiences on the [[USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77)|USS George H.W. Bush]], where he was writer-in-residence for two weeks. It has been described by [[David Finkel]], author of ''Thank You for Your Service'', as \"what we\u2019ve all come to expect from Geoff Dyer\u2014another great book. I loved everything about it. It\u2019s brilliantly observed, beautifully written, incisive, funny, and filled with stirring truths about life and the value of service.\" [[Billy Collins]], the former [[United States Poet Laureate]] and author of ''Aimless Love'', said: \"Geoff Dyer has managed to do again what he does best: insert himself into an exotic and demanding environment (sometimes, his own flat, but here, the violent wonders of an aircraft carrier) and file a report that mixes empathetic appreciation with dips into brilliant comic deflation. Welcome aboard the edifying and sometimes hilarious ship Dyer.\"\n\nDyer was made a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Literature]] in 2005.<ref>[http://www.rslit.org/people Royal Society of Literature: Current RSL Fellows (Accessdate 03-06-13)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002061545/http://www.rslit.org/people |date=2 October 2012 }}</ref> In 2014 he was elected as an Honorary Fellow of Corpus Christi College, Oxford.\n\nIn 2013 he served as the Bedell Distinguished Visiting Professor<ref>https://now.uiowa.edu/keywords/geoff-dyer</ref> at the [[University of Iowa]]'s Nonfiction Writing Program. He now teaches in the PhD program at the [[University of Southern California]].\n\n==Awards and honours==\n*1992: [[Somerset Maugham Award]] winner for ''But Beautiful''<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Books / The prize winners of 1992|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/books-the-prize-winners-of-1992-1564476.html|date=19 December 1992|website=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Society of Authors' Awards|url=https://www.societyofauthors.org/Prizes/Fiction/Somerset-Maugham/Past-winners|website=www.societyofauthors.org}}</ref>\n*1992: [[John Llewellyn Rhys Prize]] shortlisted for ''But Beautiful''{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n*1998: [[National Book Critics Circle Award]] finalist in Criticism for ''Out of Sheer Rage''<ref name=\"bookcritics\">{{cite web |url=http://bookcritics.org/awards/past_awards |title=Finalist citation for National Book Critics Circle Award |publisher=National Book Critics Circle |date=1998 |accessdate=9 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018063346/http://bookcritics.org/awards/past_awards/ |archive-date=18 October 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*2003: [[Lannan Literary Fellowship]]<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Lannan Foundation|url=https://lannan.org/literary/detail/geoff-dyer/fiction-award|website=Lannan Foundation}}</ref>\n*2004: [[WH Smith Literary Award|W H Smith Best Travel Book Award]] winner for ''Yoga For People Who Can\u2019t Be Bothered To Do It''<ref>{{cite news|first1=John|last1=Ezard|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Rowling set to win first adult book prize|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2004/jan/14/books.harrypotter|newspaper=The Guardian|date=14 January 2004|issn=0261-3077|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes-2007\">{{cite news|first1=The|last1=Editors|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Up Front|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/28/books/review/Upfront-t.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=28 October 2007|issn=0362-4331|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n*2005: Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Literature]]<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Royal Society of Literature \u00bb Geoff Dyer|url=https://rsliterature.org/fellow/geoff-dyer-3/|website=rsliterature.org}}</ref>\n*2006: Winner of the [[E. M. Forster Award]] from the American Academy of Arts and Letters{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n*2006: [[International Center of Photography]] (ICP) Infinity Award for Writing on photography for ''The Ongoing Moment''<ref name=\"nytimes-2007\"/><ref name=\"icp-infinity\">{{cite web|url = https://www.icp.org/infinity-awards/geoff-dyer | title= 2006 Infinity Award: Writing |publisher= [[International Center of Photography]] |accessdate=2 September 2016 | date = 28 April 2006}}</ref>\n*2009: ''[[GQ]]'' Writer of the Year Award<ref>{{cite web|first1=Alex|last1=Bilmes|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Geoff Dyer: Writer Of The Year|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/gq-moty-geoff-dyer-writer-of-the-year-|website=British GQ}}</ref>\n*2009: [[Bollinger Everyman Wodehouse Prize]] for Best Comic Novel for ''Jeff in Venice, Death in Varanasi''<ref>{{cite news|first1=Alison|last1=Flood|accessdate=2019-05-07|title=Geoff Dyer wins Wodehouse prize for comic fiction|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2009/may/29/geoff-dyer-wodehouse-prize-comic-fiction|newspaper=The Guardian|date=29 May 2009|issn=0261-3077|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n*2011: [[National Book Critics Circle Award]] for Criticism winner for ''Otherwise Known as the Human Condition''<ref name=\"bookcritics\"/>\n*2015: [[Windham\u2013Campbell Literature Prize]] (Non-Fiction) valued at $150,000<ref>{{cite web |url=http://windhamcampbell.org/2015/winner/edmund-de-waal |title=Prize Citation for Edmund de Waal |publisher=Windham\u2013Campbell Literature Prize |date=February 24, 2015 |accessdate=February 25, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226050843/http://windhamcampbell.org/2015/winner/edmund-de-waal |archive-date=26 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{Expand list|date=July 2015}}\n\n===Books===\n* {{cite book |author=Dyer, Geoff |authormask= |title=Ways of telling : the work of John Berger |location=London |publisher=Pluto Press |year=1986}}\n* {{cite book |author=Dyer, Geoff |authormask=1 |title=The colour of memory |location=London |publisher=Jonathan Cape |year=1989}}\n* {{cite book |author=Dyer, Geoff |authormask=1 |title=[[But Beautiful: A Book About Jazz|But beautiful : a book about jazz]] |location=London |publisher=Jonathan Cape |year=1991}}\n* {{cite book |author=Dyer, Geoff |authormask=1 |title=The search |location=London |publisher=Hamish Hamilton |year=1993}}\n* {{cite book |author=Dyer, Geoff |authormask=1 |title=The missing of the Somme |location=London