9\u201310\n| ''[[Emmerdale]]''\n| [[Mark Wylde]]\n| 158 episodes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 2013\n| ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]''\n| Dr. Madison Fielding\n| Episode: \"Revenge\"\n|-\n| ''[[Modern Family]]''\n| Professor Cooke\n| Episode: \"[[Bad Hair Day (Modern Family)|Bad Hair Day]]\"\n|-\n| ''[[DeVanity]]''\n| Richard DeVanity\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| ''[[A Prince for Christmas]]''\n| King of Balemont\n| rowspan=\"2\" | TV Movie\n|-\n| ''[[I'm Not Ready for Christmas]]''\n| Greydon DuPois\n|-\n| ''[[Castle (TV series)|Castle]]''\n| Sir Ian Rasher\n| Episode: \"The Wrong Stuff\"\n|}\n\n===Audiobooks===\n\n*''[[Anonymous Rex (novel)|Anonymous Rex]]'' by [[Eric Garcia (writer)|Eric Garcia]] (2000)\n*''The Lion of Cormarre and Other Stories: The Collected Stories of [[Arthur C. Clarke]] (1937\u20131949)'' (2001)\n*''Mimus'' by Lilli Thal (2007)\n*''Spud'' by [[John van de Ruit]] (2008)\n*''Sebastian Darke: Prince of Fools'' by [[Philip Caveney]] (2008)\n*''Spud: The Madness Continues'' by [[John van de Ruit]] (2009)\n*''[[The War of the Worlds]]'' by [[H. G. Wells]] (2012)\n\n=== Video games ===\n\n* ''[[James Bond 007: Nightfire]]'' (2002) as [[James Bond (literary character)|James Bond]]\n* [[Eragon (video game)|''Eragon'']] (2006) as Brom\n\n==Discography==\n\n* 1982: \"Charades\" on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack (as Michael Carrington)\n* 1982: \"(Love Will) Turn Back the Hands of Time\" with [[Michelle Pfeiffer]] on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Who's That Guy?\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Reproduction\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Rock-A-Hula-Luau (Summer is Coming)\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"We'll Be Together\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1995: \"Say No More (Mon Amore)\" in Alan Moyle's ''[[Empire Records]]'' (as Rex Manning)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n* [[Theater World Award]] (1979) for his performance in ''Class Enemy'' ([[Players Theatre]], [[West Village]], New York City).<ref name=\"broadway\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0001028}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|14561}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caulfield, Maxwell}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:English people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:American male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:English male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:People from Belper]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStage credits", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maxwell_Caulfield"}
{"title_page": "Ahmed Kutucu", "text_new": "{{short description|Turkish-German association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Ahmed Kutucu\n| fullname       = Ahmed Kutucu<ref name=\"FIFA\">{{cite web |url=http://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FU17/2017/PDF/FU17_2017_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=FIFA U-17 World Cup India 2017 \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |page=23 |date=28 October 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n| image          = Ahmed Kutucu 2019.jpg\n| caption        = Kutucu with [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in 2019\n| height         = 1.81 m\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|2000|3|1}}\n| birth_place    = [[Gelsenkirchen]], Germany\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|Centre-forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| clubnumber     = 15\n| youthyears1    = 2003\u20132006\n| youthclubs1    = Sportreunde Haverkamp\n| youthyears2    = 2006\u20132011\n| youthclubs2    = [[Rot-Weiss Essen]]\n| youthyears3    = 2011\u2013\n| youthclubs3    = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| years1         = 2018\u2013\n| clubs1         = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04 II]]\n| caps1          = 30\n| goals1         = 5\n| years2         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs2         = [[FC Schalke 04 II|Schalke 04]]\n| caps2          = 1\n| goals2         = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2017\n| nationalteam1  = [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2018\n| nationalteam2  = [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Turkey U19]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam3  = [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey U21]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 3\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam4  = [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]\n| nationalcaps4  = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| pcupdate       = 00:53, 9 March 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = 20 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Kutucu''' (born 1 March 2000) is a Turkish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|centre-forward]] for [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].<ref name=\"WF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/ahmed-kutucu/|title=Ahmed Kutucu|website=worldfootball.net|accessdate=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nKutucu began his youth career with Sportreunde Haverkamp in 2003, before moving to the youth team of [[Rot-Weiss Essen]] in 2006. In 2011, he joined the youth sector of [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://schalke04.de/knappenschmiede/ahmed-kutucu/ |title=Ahmed Kutucu |website=schalke04.de |publisher=[[FC Schalke 04]] |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=German |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211200245/https://schalke04.de/knappenschmiede/ahmed-kutucu/ |archive-date=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 December 2018, Kutucu made his first team debut for Schalke in the [[UEFA Champions League]], coming on as a substitute in the 72nd minute for [[Cedric Teuchert]] in the 1\u20130 home win against [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000980/match=2025140/index.html |title=UEFA Champions League: Schalke v Lokomotiv Moskva |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=11 December 2018 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref> He scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal on 22 December 2018, coming on as a substitute in the 73rd minute to replace [[Yevhen Konoplyanka]] in a 3\u20131 away win against [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vfb-stuttgart-schalke-live-line-ups-stats-christian-gentner-weston-mckennie-fantasy-2688-1048|title=Schalke end 2018 on a high and leave Stuttgart struggling|website=bundesliga.com|date=22 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKutucu was included in [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup squads#Turkey|Turkey's squad]] for the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in India.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27865 |title=U17 Milli Tak\u0131m\u0131, D\u00fcnya Kupas\u0131 haz\u0131rl\u0131klar\u0131na ba\u015flad\u0131 |trans-title=U17 national team started World Cup preparations |website=TFF.org |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=16 September 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=Turkish |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805233805/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27865 |archive-date=5 August 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 6 October 2017 in the first group match, opening the scoring for Turkey with a header in the 18th minute against [[New Zealand national under-17 football team|New Zealand]], with the match finishing as a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/u17-h-wm-2017-indien-gruppe-b-neuseeland-tuerkei/ |title=New Zealand \u2013 Turkey 1:1 (U17 World Cup 2017 India, Group B) |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |date=6 October 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref> He played in Turkey's remaining two matches, where they were eliminated in the tournament's group stage.<ref name=\"WF\"/> The following year, he was included in [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship squads#Turkey|Turkey's squad]] for the [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Finland.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=274&ftxtID=29511 |title=U19 Milli Tak\u0131m\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n Avrupa \u015eampiyonas\u0131 Finalleri aday kadrosu a\u00e7\u0131kland\u0131 |trans-title=U19 national team's European Championship squad nominees announced |website=TFF.org |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=Turkish |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703051124/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=274&ftxtID=29511 |archive-date=3 July 2018}}</ref> He played all three matches for Turkey, with the team being eliminated in the group stage.<ref name=\"WF\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played on 7 March 2020.|<ref name=\"WF\"/>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup!!colspan=\"2\"|Europe!!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]||[[2018\u201319 FC Schalke 04 season|2018\u201319]]||[[Bundesliga]]||13||2||2||1||1{{efn|Appearance in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||16||3\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 FC Schalke 04 season|2019\u201320]]||Bundesliga||17||3||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||20||3\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total!!30!!5!!5!!1!!1!!0!!36!!6\n|}\n{{Notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played on 17 November 2019.|<ref name=\"WF\"/>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2019||1||0\n|-\n!Total!!1!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{UEFA player|250121000}}\n* {{Soccerway|ahmed-kutucu/482386}}\n* {{DFB|352767<!-- ahmed-kutucu -->}}\n* {{TFF player|2042328}}\n* {{Kicker|<!-- ahmet-kutucu- -->100145}}\n\n{{FC Schalke 04 squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kutucu, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Gelsenkirchen]]\n[[Category:Footballers from North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n[[Category:Turkish footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkey international footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkey under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkey youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:FC Schalke 04 players]]\n[[Category:FC Schalke 04 II players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Turkish-German association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Ahmed Kutucu\n| fullname       = Ahmed Kutucu<ref name=\"FIFA\">{{cite web |url=http://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FU17/2017/PDF/FU17_2017_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=FIFA U-17 World Cup India 2017 \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |page=23 |date=28 October 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n| image          = Ahmed Kutucu 2019.jpg\n| caption        = Kutucu with [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in 2019\n| height         = 1.81 m\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|2000|3|1}}\n| birth_place    = [[Gelsenkirchen]], Germany\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|Centre-forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| clubnumber     = 15\n| youthyears1    = 2003\u20132006\n| youthclubs1    = Sportreunde Haverkamp\n| youthyears2    = 2006\u20132011\n| youthclubs2    = [[Rot-Weiss Essen]]\n| youthyears3    = 2011\u2013\n| youthclubs3    = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| years1         = 2018\u2013\n| clubs1         = [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| caps1          = 30\n| goals1         = 5\n| years2         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs2         = [[FC Schalke 04 II|Schalke 04 II]]\n| caps2          = 1\n| goals2         = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2017\n| nationalteam1  = [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2018\n| nationalteam2  = [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Turkey U19]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam3  = [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey U21]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 3\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam4  = [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]\n| nationalcaps4  = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| pcupdate       = 00:53, 9 March 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = 20 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Kutucu''' (born 1 March 2000) is a Turkish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|centre-forward]] for [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].<ref name=\"WF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/ahmed-kutucu/|title=Ahmed Kutucu|website=worldfootball.net|accessdate=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nKutucu began his youth career with Sportreunde Haverkamp in 2003, before moving to the youth team of [[Rot-Weiss Essen]] in 2006. In 2011, he joined the youth sector of [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://schalke04.de/knappenschmiede/ahmed-kutucu/ |title=Ahmed Kutucu |website=schalke04.de |publisher=[[FC Schalke 04]] |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=German |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211200245/https://schalke04.de/knappenschmiede/ahmed-kutucu/ |archive-date=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 December 2018, Kutucu made his first team debut for Schalke in the [[UEFA Champions League]], coming on as a substitute in the 72nd minute for [[Cedric Teuchert]] in the 1\u20130 home win against [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000980/match=2025140/index.html |title=UEFA Champions League: Schalke v Lokomotiv Moskva |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=11 December 2018 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref> He scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal on 22 December 2018, coming on as a substitute in the 73rd minute to replace [[Yevhen Konoplyanka]] in a 3\u20131 away win against [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vfb-stuttgart-schalke-live-line-ups-stats-christian-gentner-weston-mckennie-fantasy-2688-1048|title=Schalke end 2018 on a high and leave Stuttgart struggling|website=bundesliga.com|date=22 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKutucu was included in [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup squads#Turkey|Turkey's squad]] for the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in India.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27865 |title=U17 Milli Tak\u0131m\u0131, D\u00fcnya Kupas\u0131 haz\u0131rl\u0131klar\u0131na ba\u015flad\u0131 |trans-title=U17 national team started World Cup preparations |website=TFF.org |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=16 September 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=Turkish |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805233805/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27865 |archive-date=5 August 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 6 October 2017 in the first group match, opening the scoring for Turkey with a header in the 18th minute against [[New Zealand national under-17 football team|New Zealand]], with the match finishing as a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/u17-h-wm-2017-indien-gruppe-b-neuseeland-tuerkei/ |title=New Zealand \u2013 Turkey 1:1 (U17 World Cup 2017 India, Group B) |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |date=6 October 2017 |access-date=11 December 2018}}</ref> He played in Turkey's remaining two matches, where they were eliminated in the tournament's group stage.<ref name=\"WF\"/> The following year, he was included in [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship squads#Turkey|Turkey's squad]] for the [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Finland.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=274&ftxtID=29511 |title=U19 Milli Tak\u0131m\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n Avrupa \u015eampiyonas\u0131 Finalleri aday kadrosu a\u00e7\u0131kland\u0131 |trans-title=U19 national team's European Championship squad nominees announced |website=TFF.org |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=11 December 2018 |language=Turkish |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703051124/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=274&ftxtID=29511 |archive-date=3 July 2018}}</ref> He played all three matches for Turkey, with the team being eliminated in the group stage.<ref name=\"WF\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played on 7 March 2020.|<ref name=\"WF\"/>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup!!colspan=\"2\"|Europe!!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]||[[2018\u201319 FC Schalke 04 season|2018\u201319]]||[[Bundesliga]]||13||2||2||1||1{{efn|Appearance in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||16||3\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 FC Schalke 04 season|2019\u201320]]||Bundesliga||17||3||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||20||3\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total!!30!!5!!5!!1!!1!!0!!36!!6\n|}\n{{Notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played on 17 November 2019.|<ref name=\"WF\"/>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2019||1||0\n|-\n!Total!!1!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{UEFA player|250121000}}\n* {{Soccerway|ahmed-kutucu/482386}}\n* {{DFB|352767<!-- ahmed-kutucu -->}}\n* {{TFF player|2042328}}\n* {{Kicker|<!-- ahmet-kutucu- -->100145}}\n\n{{FC Schalke 04 squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kutucu, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Gelsenkirchen]]\n[[Category:Footballers